{"talk":{"id":1626,"name":"Nina Tandon: Could tissue engineering mean personalized medicine?","description":"Each of our bodies is utterly unique, which is a lovely thought until it comes to treating an illness -- when every body reacts differently, often unpredictably, to standard treatment. Tissue engineer Nina Tandon talks about a possible solution: Using pluripotent stem cells to make personalized models of organs on which to test new drugs and treatments, and storing them on computer chips. (Call it extremely personalized medicine.)","slug":"nina_tandon_could_tissue_engineering_mean_personalized_medicine","recorded_at":"2012-06-26 00:00:00","published_at":"2012-12-06 16:07:07","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:37:05","viewed_count":1115078,"emailed_count":87,"event":{"id":141,"name":"TEDGlobal 2012"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/4bf7a74e6957744c80271877160796263fb65761_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/4bf7a74e6957744c80271877160796263fb65761_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/4bf7a74e6957744c80271877160796263fb65761_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/4bf7a74e6957744c80271877160796263fb65761_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/9197769047d71b6415d0d08c5b1248ae6360cb3a_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/NinaTandon_2012G-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":3167475,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/NinaTandon_2012G-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":8658971,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/NinaTandon_2012G-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":15218884,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"450k":{